OL,3,C'I left hospital empty-handed
OL,4,Ceveryday': Bed shortage for parents of
OL,5,Csick babies
OL,7,FNatasha Schulz-Apps' son Teddy was
OL,8,Fborn at 26 weeks and required care in
OL,9,Ftwo hospitals, where he stayed for
OL,10,Fthree months.
OL,12,FWhile both hospitals had some
OL,13,Faccommodation available, there were
OL,14,Fmore babies than beds for parents
OL,15,Fmeaning Natasha was able to stay some
OL,16,Fnights but had to return home on
OL,17,Fothers.
