OL,3,C'I left hospital empty-handed
OL,4,Ceveryday': Bed shortage for parents of
OL,5,Csick babies
OL,7,FA survey by Bliss of 140 neonatal
OL,8,Funits across England found that 44% do
OL,9,Fnot even have temporary beds - such as
OL,10,Freclining armchairs or fold-out beds -
OL,11,Fnext to at least one cot.
OL,13,F"I was there from 7am to 8pm every day
OL,14,Fjust sitting on an ordinary chair" Ms
OL,15,FSchulz-Apps said.
OL,17,F"Staff would say to you 'mum you're no
OL,18,Fgood here, you need to go home and
OL,19,Fsleep' but you'd go home and you
OL,20,Fcouldn't sleep. I'd keep ringing the
OL,21,Fhospital to check he was ok."
