OL,3,C'I left hospital empty-handed
OL,4,Ceveryday': Bed shortage for parents of
OL,5,Csick babies
OL,7,F"It's the most common experience for
OL,8,Fparents of babies in intensive care
OL,9,Fthat they are either not able to stay
OL,10,Fat all or cannot stay the whole time.
OL,12,F"Every parent I speak to says one of
OL,13,Fthe most heartbreaking things is
OL,14,Fleaving a baby at night to go home."
OL,16,FBliss have launched a campaign called
OL,17,F'Families Kept Apart' and have asked
OL,18,Fthe NHS and government to put
OL,19,Fsolutions in place to enable parents
OL,20,Fto stay with their babies overnight in
OL,21,Fhospital.
